---
import Article from "../../layouts/Article.astro";
import AffiliateButton from "../../components/AffiliateButton.astro";
import NewsletterSignup from "../../components/NewsletterSignup.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
import Schema from "../../components/Schema.astro";
import { AFFILIATE } from "../../data/affiliate.ts";
import { articleSchema } from "../../lib/schema.ts";

const title =
  "Beauty of Joseon Aqua-Fresh vs Daily Tinted Fluid: Which One Should You Buy?";
const description =
  "Comparing two of Beauty of Joseon's best sunscreens: the untinted Aqua-Fresh SPF 50+ vs the new Daily Tinted Fluid SPF 40. Same brand, totally different purpose. Here's which to pick.";

const articleData = articleSchema({
  headline: title,
  description,
  image: "/products/boj-aqua-fresh.jpg",
  url: "/compare/beauty-of-joseon-aqua-fresh-vs-daily-tinted/",
  datePublished: "2026-05-01",
  articleSection: "Comparison",
});
---

<Article
  title={title}
  description={description}
  eyebrow="Comparison"
  published="May 2026"
  readTime="5 min"
  heroTitle="BoJ Aqua-Fresh vs BoJ Daily Tinted: same brand, two very different products"
>
  <Schema data={articleData} />
  <Breadcrumbs
    items={[
      { name: "Compare", path: "/compare/" },
      { name: "BoJ Aqua-Fresh vs Daily Tinted", path: "/compare/beauty-of-joseon-aqua-fresh-vs-daily-tinted/" },
    ]}
  />

  <p>
    Beauty of Joseon makes two of the most talked-about sunscreens on the
    market — and they couldn't be more different. The <strong>Relief Sun
    Aqua-Fresh</strong> is a bare-skin SPF 50+ with zero tint, built for
    people who want invisible, weightless protection. The <strong>Daily
    Tinted Fluid</strong> is BoJ's first foray into tinted SPF, offering 12
    shades that replace your complexion step entirely.
  </p>
  <p>
    Both are under $20. Both are from the same cult Korean brand. But they
    serve completely different purposes — and picking the wrong one is a
    common mistake.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 not-prose">
    <div class="bg-cream-100 rounded-xl p-6 border border-sun-200/40">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sun-700 mb-2">
        If you want the best bare-skin SPF
      </div>
      <div class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-ink-900 mb-2">
        → BoJ Aqua-Fresh
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-600 mb-4">
        SPF 50+ PA++++, zero cast, watery texture. The original for a reason.
      </p>
      <AffiliateButton
        href={AFFILIATE.bojAquaFresh.amazon}
        label="Buy Aqua-Fresh ($13.50)"
        size="sm"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="bg-ink-900 rounded-xl p-6 text-cream-50">
      <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sun-400 mb-2">
        If you want SPF + a shade match
      </div>
      <div class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-2">
        → BoJ Daily Tinted Fluid
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-cream-200/80 mb-4">
        12 shades, dewy coverage, replaces your foundation step.
      </p>
      <AffiliateButton
        href={AFFILIATE.bojDailyTinted.amazon}
        label="Buy Daily Tinted ($16)"
        size="sm"
        variant="secondary"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Side-by-side specs</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-ink-900/8">
    <table class="w-full text-sm min-w-[480px]">
      <thead class="bg-cream-100">
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-900 px-4 py-3"></th>
          <th class="text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-900 px-4 py-3">Aqua-Fresh</th>
          <th class="text-left font-display font-semibold text-ink-900 px-4 py-3">Daily Tinted Fluid</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-ink-700">
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Price</td><td class="px-4 py-3">$13.50 / 50ml</td><td class="px-4 py-3">$16 / 30ml</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Price per ml</td><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">$0.27</td><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">$0.53</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">SPF</td><td class="px-4 py-3">50+ PA++++</td><td class="px-4 py-3">40 (US formula)</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Filters</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Chemical (Tinosorb S+)</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Chemical (US formula)</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Tinted?</td><td class="px-4 py-3">No</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Yes — 12 shades</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Finish</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Dewy, watery, invisible</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Dewy, natural glow</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Best for</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Oily &amp; combination skin</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Dry to normal</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Under makeup</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Excellent primer base</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Replaces makeup step</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Amazon ratings</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4.8★ · 6,503 reviews</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4.0★ · 1,796 reviews</td></tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-ink-900/5"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-ink-500">Fragrance</td><td class="px-4 py-3">None</td><td class="px-4 py-3">None</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Round 1: Sun protection</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Winner: Aqua-Fresh.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    This one isn't close. Aqua-Fresh is SPF 50+ with PA++++ — the highest UVA
    rating in the Asian system, and it uses Tinosorb S and Uvinul A Plus, next-generation
    photostable filters. The Daily Tinted Fluid is SPF 40 in the US version
    (the Korean import version differs), with a simpler filter stack. If protection
    is your primary goal, Aqua-Fresh wins on every metric.
  </p>

  <h2>Round 2: Shade range</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Winner: Daily Tinted Fluid, by a mile.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Aqua-Fresh has no shade range — it's completely untinted. The Daily Tinted
    Fluid offers 12 shades including true cool and neutral options that are
    genuinely rare in K-beauty SPF. If you want your sunscreen to even out
    your skin tone, there's only one answer here.
  </p>

  <h2>Round 3: Finish and feel</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Winner: Aqua-Fresh for oily skin; Daily Tinted for dry skin.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Both give you a dewy, luminous finish — but Aqua-Fresh's watery texture is
    significantly lighter. On oily or combination skin, that weightlessness is
    the advantage. The Daily Tinted Fluid has more body (it's carrying 12 shades
    of pigment), which makes it sit better on drier skin types. In hot, humid weather,
    the Daily Tinted can feel heavy on combination-to-oily skin by early afternoon.
  </p>

  <h2>Round 4: Value for money</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Winner: Aqua-Fresh.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Aqua-Fresh costs <strong>$0.27 per ml</strong>. The Daily Tinted Fluid is
    <strong>$0.53 per ml</strong> — nearly twice the price for half the volume.
    And Aqua-Fresh delivers a higher SPF in the deal. The Daily Tinted justifies
    its premium through pigment and shade range — but on pure sun-protection
    economics, Aqua-Fresh is the better buy.
  </p>

  <h2>Round 5: Under makeup</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Winner: Depends on your goal.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Aqua-Fresh is our go-to primer base — it doesn't pill, creates a slightly
    tacky surface foundation grips to, and the dewy finish makes skin look
    plump and prepped. On a full-makeup day, use Aqua-Fresh.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Daily Tinted Fluid is designed to replace your complexion step on
    no-makeup or low-effort days. On those days — it works beautifully. But
    if you want to layer foundation on top, the lighter Aqua-Fresh is the
    better base.
  </p>

  <h2>Who should buy which</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Buy Aqua-Fresh if:</strong> You already have a foundation or tinted
      moisturiser you love, you want the best possible SPF under $20, or your
      skin runs oily.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Buy Daily Tinted if:</strong> You want one product that provides
      SPF + coverage, you've struggled to find a K-beauty tint in your shade,
      or you prefer dry skin and a natural glow finish.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Buy both if:</strong> You're a serious skincare person. Use
      Aqua-Fresh as your daily SPF under makeup and reach for the Daily Tinted
      on easy, no-makeup days.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="not-prose my-8 p-5 bg-cream-100 rounded-xl border border-sun-200/40">
    <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sun-700 mb-2">
      The Bottom Line
    </div>
    <p class="text-ink-700 leading-relaxed m-0">
      If you can only pick one: <strong>Aqua-Fresh</strong>. Better SPF, lighter texture,
      half the cost per ml. Add the Daily Tinted once you've found your shade.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="my-10 not-prose grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
    <AffiliateButton
      href={AFFILIATE.bojAquaFresh.amazon}
      label="Buy BoJ Aqua-Fresh ($13.50)"
    />
    <AffiliateButton
      href={AFFILIATE.bojDailyTinted.amazon}
      label="Buy BoJ Daily Tinted ($16)"
      variant="secondary"
    />
  </div>

  <NewsletterSignup variant="compact" />

  <h2>Related reading</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/reviews/beauty-of-joseon-relief-sun-aqua-fresh/">Full BoJ Aqua-Fresh review</a></li>
    <li><a href="/reviews/beauty-of-joseon-daily-tinted-fluid/">Full BoJ Daily Tinted Fluid review</a></li>
    <li><a href="/compare/boj-aqua-fresh-vs-merit-uniform/">BoJ Aqua-Fresh vs Merit The Uniform</a></li>
    <li><a href="/">All 9 tinted sunscreens ranked for 2026</a></li>
  </ul>
</Article>
